<subSubSection id="02C66578FFE2FFA3FC959A6D6ACB7B3A" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FC959A6D6ACB7B3A" blockId="15.[831,1436,1577,1628]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
1956. 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE2FFA3FC289A6D6C117B5C" authority="SAID &amp; KENAWY" authorityName="SAID &amp; KENAWY" authorityYear="1956" box="[898,1308,1577,1598]" class="Globothalamea" family="Verneuilinidae" genus="Gaudryina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Lituolida" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="elegantissima">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FC289A6D6D7E7B5F" box="[898,1139,1577,1598]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Gaudryina elegantissima</emphasis>
SAID &amp; KENAWY
</taxonomicName>
, p. 123, pl. 1, fig. 21.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02C66578FFE2FFA3FC959AC06D837ADF" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FC959AC06DC27B9C" blockId="15.[831,1437,1668,1982]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FC959AC06ABD7BFD" bold="true" box="[831,944,1668,1692]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by an elongate test. The earlier portion of the test is triserial and becoming biserial early in the development. The chambers are very gradually increasing in size as added.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FC959B416D837ADF" blockId="15.[831,1437,1668,1982]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FC959B416D617A7C" bold="true" box="[831,1132,1797,1821]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally identified in the Late Cretaceous of 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFE2FFA3FB9E9B616D667A5C" box="[1076,1131,1829,1853]" country="Egypt" name="Shamal Sina'" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Sinai</collectingRegion>
by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956). In the study area, it is recorded in the Maastricthian zones 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FCEA9B226D637A1F" box="[832,1134,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
(
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE2FFA3FCED9B226D637A1F" box="[839,1134,1894,1918]" class="Globothalamea" family="Globotruncanidae" genus="Globotruncana" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="aegyptiaca">Globotruncana aegyptiaca</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FB1A9B226C917A1C" box="[1200,1436,1894,1917]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE2FFA3FB1A9B226C997A1C" authorityName="Zone (CHERIF &amp; ISMAIL" authorityYear="1991" box="[1200,1428,1894,1917]" class="Globothalamea" family="Globotruncanidae" genus="Gansserina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="gansseri">Gansserina gansseri</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
and in the Paleocene zones 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FBD29BC26C917AFF" box="[1144,1436,1926,1950]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
(
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE2FFA3FB2A9BC26C917AFF" box="[1152,1436,1926,1950]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="trinidadensis">Morozovella trinidadensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FCC79BE26D8A7ADF" box="[877,1159,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE2FFA3FCC79BE26D727ADF" box="[877,1151,1958,1982]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="velascoensis">Morozovella velascoensis</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
